    <section id="culture" class="culture">
        <h2 style="text-align: center; color: #f1c40f;">Indian Cultural Heritage</h2>
        <p style="text-align: center; max-width: 700px; margin: 1rem auto; color: #f1f2f6;">
            India’s culture includes its languages, cuisine, attire, festivals, music, and art forms like dance and architecture. It is a living example of unity in diversity.
        </p>

        <div class="culture-grid">
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>🎉 Festivals</h3>
                <p>India celebrates a range of festivals like Diwali, Eid, Pongal, Holi, and Onam — each with its own vibrant rituals.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>🍛 Cuisine</h3>
                <p>From spicy curries of the south to the rich sweets of the north, India’s regional food is as diverse as its people.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>🎶 Music & Instruments</h3>
                <p>Classical forms like Hindustani and Carnatic blend with instruments like sitar, tabla, veena, and dhol.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>👘 Traditional Clothing</h3>
                <p>Each region wears distinct attire — saris, lehengas, dhotis, and turbans — often adorned with handwoven fabrics.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>🗣️ Languages</h3>
                <p>India has 22 official languages and hundreds of dialects, reflecting its multi-ethnic identity and history.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="culture-card">
                <h3>🏛️ Architecture</h3>
                <p>From ancient temples and Mughal forts to colonial buildings, India's structures are living museums of its legacy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
